						<summary>

						<p>This is much damaged. It seems to record some gift made to ‘Paramasvāmi who was pleased to have his happy abode’ at Tiruviyalūr, by one Aḻiñjillaiyyaṉ of the <hi rend="italic">Kōdaṇḍarāmat-tanichchēvagam</hi> of the king, which probably means a body of selected retainers.</p>						

						</summary>
